10:
Oooh, here we go! Is the World Flipper 
really going to open the way to other 
worlds? This will be so much fun!
31:
Stella, this is phenomenal!
Everything is sparkly and glowy and—
Ooooh! WOW! Look, look!
34:
Yes, yes, now you four behave 
yourselves.
43:
...I'm sorry, Light. I don't think this is it 
either.
47: That is no fault of yours.
49:
One more world stands between us 
and my home. I am beginning to think 
destiny stays our hand.
54:
Yeah, Light's right. We're so close to 
filling out the star chart, we might as 
well finish it off.
56:
That should restore Light's power, 
right?
61:
I'm sure we are all shaken by the 
sorceress' words, but she is not to be 
trusted.
63:
No matter who she is or what she 
wants, we know OUR goal, and what we 
must do to achieve it.
72:
Are you ready yet? The World Flipper is 
working, is it not? How do I use it?
76:
Can I touch it?
...I am going to touch it.
79:
You most certainly are not!
Goodness, child, they were having an 
important conversation!
83:
I'll activate the World Flipper. Please 
wait a moment.
99:
This will be quite convenient. It should 
certainly make it easier to travel back 
and forth from our home.
108:
That was a long adventure! I believe it 
is about time we headed home. Thank 
you for all the help!
112:
You have my gratitude as well. Thank 
you for taking care of her.
121:
Time you headed home...
You mean back to Inaho's mother?
125:
Oh! Oh, no. Mother.
Sh-she will be SO mad when she hears 
what happened.
129:
But! But I also have so much to tell 
her! 
Mother never liked humans, but this 
time for sure—I shall change her 
mind!
135:
I can already see how that's going to 
end.
139:
You are m-my...
My very first friends!
148:
Yeah, we'll definitely see you again 
someday!
151:
I don't know. It WOULD be nice and 
peaceful around here without foxes 
pulling pranks.
156: Oh? Sounds like someone is jealous!
158:
Very well, I shall allow you to be my 
friend as well, diviner!
163:
Farewell, everyone! 'Til we meet 
again!
...There better be souvenirs to swap!
167:
I sincerely hope to see you all again, 
dearies.
176:
The bonds you made here will last 
a lifetime.
181:
You mean I'll be stuck dealing with her 
forever? I have enough to deal with 
already...
186:
Oh, yeah. You were trying to exorcise 
them, and now you've basically given 
'em the keys to the place!
189:
I don't have time to waste chasing 
Inaho around. There are more 
pressing matters at hand
—Orochi's spirit rejoined the flow of 
energy coursing through these 
mountains.
191:
The shogunate is already scrambling 
to investigate what caused the 
sudden change in the East's energy 
currents.
195:
Um... You. You caused the sudden 
change in energy currents.
198:
They don't know that.
I'm innocent until proven guilty!
200:
I suppose the ninjas will put two and 
two together, but they owe me.
203:
I can only imagine they'd prefer their 
OWN involvement stayed secret, so 
we're in the same boat. They can't 
touch me.
210:
I'll have my work cut out for me, but 
we've no option but to get used to the 
yokai and other supernatural beings 
pouring back into the East.
214:
I would be happy to lend what aid 
I can.
218:
I'm certain the two of you will be just 
fine.
220: It's high time we got moving ourselves.
223:
Yeah, I'm sure you're itching to get 
back home, huh?
227:
I wish you the best of luck in your 
travels!
235:
I- I also wish you the best on your 
journey!
...Thank you for everything.
239: Thank you too, Suizen. Take care.
243:
Don't push yourself too hard, okay? 
Take good care of yourself!
248: Till we meet again—to the next world!
